# Portfolio Starter Kit 🚀
A cutting-edge, minimalist portfolio and blog template designed for developers and creatives, built with the latest web technologies.
![Portfolio Starter Kit Preview](/public/images/portfolio-preview.png)
**Transform your online presence with a sleek, high-performance personal website.**
## ✨ Features
- **Blazing Fast Performance**: Built on Next.js 14 with App Router for optimal loading speeds
- **Responsive Design**: Looks great on all devices from mobile to desktop
- **Modern Stack**: Next.js, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS v4
- **Blog Ready**: MDX support for rich content with code syntax highlighting
- **SEO Optimized**: Dynamic sitemap, robots.txt, and metadata optimization
- **Dark Mode**: Built-in dark mode with reactive animation effects
- **Easy Customization**: Simple structure makes it easy to customize to your needs
- **RSS Support**: Automatically generates RSS feed for your content
- **OG Image Generation**: Dynamic Open Graph images for better social sharing
- **Analytics Ready**: Integrated with Vercel Analytics and Speed Insights
## 🚀 Quick Start
### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v18+ recommended)
- npm, yarn, or pnpm
### Installation
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/portfolio-starter-kit.git
cd portfolio-starter-kit
# Install dependencies
npm install  # or yarn install or pnpm install
# Start development server
npm run dev  # or yarn dev or pnpm dev
```
🌐 Your site is now live at [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)!
## 📝 Adding Content
### Blog Posts
Add new blog posts by creating MDX files in the `app/blog/posts/` directory. Each post should include frontmatter with title, date, and other metadata.
### Projects
Edit the `app/projects/page.tsx` file to update your project showcase.
## 🎨 Customization
### Styling with Tailwind CSS
- Fully customizable design system
- Responsive and mobile-first approach
- Edit `tailwind.config.js` to personalize your theme
### Typography
- Geist font for modern, clean typography
- Easy font and style customization
- Configure in global CSS and Tailwind settings
## 📦 Deployment
This project is optimized for deployment on [Vercel](https://vercel.com/), but can be deployed on any platform that supports Next.js.
```bash
# Build for production
npm run build
# or
yarn build
# or
pnpm build
# Start production server
npm start
# or
yarn start
# or
pnpm start
```
